## Before Taking Action \'97 What We Need to Understand\
\
### Question 1: What does the website look like to a first-time visitor?\
\
Right now, a first-time visitor from Instagram lands on cultive.city and sees... what? Without knowing the exact first-screen experience, the possible failure points are:\
\
| Possible Problem | Symptom |\
|-----------------|---------|\
| No clear value proposition above the fold | Visitor doesn't understand what CULTIVE is in 3 seconds \uc0\u8594  bounces |\
| No sign-up CTA visible without scrolling | Visitor browses, enjoys it, but is never asked to sign up |\
| Blur wall is too aggressive | Visitor hits the wall, feels blocked, leaves |\
| Blur wall is too passive | Visitor browses 10 free events, gets what they need, leaves |\
| Sign-up process is too heavy | Visitor wants to sign up but the friction (email + password + verification) kills it |\
| No reason to sign up | Visitor doesn't see what signing up gives them beyond "see more events" |\
| Site loads slowly on mobile | Visitor bounces before the page finishes loading |\
\
**Shane needs to answer:** What is the exact experience for a first-time mobile visitor? What do they see? What's the first CTA? How many clicks to sign up? What happens after they sign up?\
\
### Question 2: What is the actual sign-up value proposition?\
\
Eugene's review already identified this. The current copy is functional, not emotional. But more than copy \'97 what does a user GAIN by signing up?\
\
| What We Offer Now | What a User Actually Wants |\
|-------------------|---------------------------|\
| See all events | "I can already see 10 for free" |\
| Save favourites | "I can screenshot or send to myself on WhatsApp" |\
| Submit events | "Why would I do that?" |\
| Earn credits | "Credits for what? I don't understand the value" |\
\
**The sign-up value proposition needs to be obvious and immediate.** Not "free to join" \'97 that's a cost, not a benefit. The benefit has to be something they can't get without an account.\
\
### Question 3: Who is the target user, and are we reaching them?\
\
6,166 people reached. Who are they?\
\
| If they're... | Then... |\
|--------------|---------|\
| General HK Instagram browsers | Low intent. They saw a post, thought "cool," moved on. They're not looking for an events platform. |\
| Active event-goers | Higher intent. They attend events regularly. If the content spoke to them, they'd click through. |\
| Expats exploring HK | Medium intent. Looking for things to do but may not be ready to commit to a platform. |\
| People who already have event sources | Low intent. They get their info from TimeOut, WhatsApp groups, friends. CULTIVE doesn't solve a problem they feel. |\
\
**We don't know who they are.** And until we do, every strategy is a guess.\
\
### Question 4: Is the problem awareness or conversion?\
\
Two very different problems with very different solutions.\
\
| If the problem is AWARENESS | If the problem is CONVERSION |\
|----------------------------|----------------------------|\
| People don't know CULTIVE exists | People see CULTIVE but don't sign up |\
| Fix: more reach, more content, paid ads, PR, KOLs | Fix: better sign-up flow, stronger value prop, lower friction |\
| Andy and William's connections help here | Andy and William's connections don't help here |\
| Scale solves it | Product solves it |\
\
**The data says the problem is conversion, not awareness.** 6,166 people reached. 352 visited the profile. People are finding CULTIVE. They're just not signing up.\
\
