\
## What This Means for Andy and William\
\
Andy and William are powerful additions to the team. Their network, media experience, data expertise, insurance/business connections, and investment capacity are genuine assets. But deploying them now on traffic and awareness is like pouring water into a bucket with a hole.\
\
### What They Should NOT Do Yet\
\
| Action | Why Not |\
|--------|---------|\
| Push traffic to the site via their networks | If the site converts at 1 sign-up per 6,166 reach, sending more traffic just means more people who don't sign up. |\
| Invest in paid ads | Same problem. Paid traffic that doesn't convert is money burned. |\
| Pitch sponsors/partners | The pitch is "we have X users." With 1 sign-up, there's nothing to pitch. |\
| PR push | Press coverage drives traffic. Traffic that doesn't convert is wasted coverage. |\
\
### What They SHOULD Do Right Now\
\
**Before the conversion problem is fixed:**\
\
| Action | Why | Time |\
|--------|-----|------|\
| **Understand the product** | Spend 30 minutes on cultive.city as a first-time user. What's the experience? Would YOU sign up? Why or why not? Their business operator perspective is valuable here. | 1 hour |\
| **Give honest feedback** | They run multiple businesses. They know what converts. Have them review the site, the sign-up flow, the value proposition. Fresh eyes catch things the team is too close to see. | 1 hour |\
| **Test the sign-up flow themselves** | Walk through it on mobile. Time it. Count the steps. Note every point of friction. | 30 minutes |\
| **Ask their networks one question** | Not "sign up for CULTIVE" \'97 just "what do you use to find events in Hong Kong?" The answers reveal the competitive landscape and the actual pain point. | Ongoing conversations |\
\
**After the conversion problem is fixed (and only after):**\
\
| Action | Why | Impact |\
|--------|-----|--------|\
| **Open their network to CULTIVE** | Introduce the platform to their elite HK connections. These are likely the exact demographic \'97 high-income, culture-active, socially connected. | High-quality sign-ups |\
| **Traffic and awareness** | Use their media experience to drive targeted traffic. Not mass \'97 targeted. | Right users, not just more users |\
| **Business development** | Their business connections become venue partners, sponsors, and advertisers. | Revenue |\
| **Investment conversations** | If the product converts and retains, investment becomes a conversation about scaling, not surviving. | Growth capital |\
| **Media leverage** | Their media connections become press coverage, features, and cross-promotion. | Credibility + reach |\
\
